{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775905222879,"sessionID":"ses_283ce9db5ffevQxE8Wzt5NGV5h","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3330db001Luty2t5EEQ0sAF","messageID":"msg_d7c32e63d001RgBu7uPo4rVrWX","sessionID":"ses_283ce9db5ffevQxE8Wzt5NGV5h","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905224453,"sessionID":"ses_283ce9db5ffevQxE8Wzt5NGV5h","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3332aa001jCCmYVHcGaQEm0","messageID":"msg_d7c32e63d001RgBu7uPo4rVrWX","sessionID":"ses_283ce9db5ffevQxE8Wzt5NGV5h","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-027  \n6: **Module:** sdk-python  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Target:** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`, `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `agentcube/clients/`\n10: \n11: This delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`), which provides Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Package Layout\n16: \n17: | Path | Role |\n18: |------|------|\n19: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n20: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n21: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n22: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n23: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n24: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n25: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n26: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n27: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n28: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n29: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n30: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n31: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Requirements\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient Lifecycle Management\n38: \n39: **GIVEN** the need to manage Code Interpreter sessions  \n40: **WHEN** constructing and using `CodeInterpreterClient`  \n41: **THEN** the system SHALL either reuse an existing `session_id` or create a new session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initialize `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Context Manager Cleanup\n44: \n45: **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager  \n46: **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)  \n47: **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session.\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Data Plane Init Failure After Session Create\n50: \n51: **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded  \n52: **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception  \n53: **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the exception.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Router URL Required\n56: \n57: **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set  \n58: **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs  \n59: **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter Operations\n64: \n65: **GIVEN** a connected Code Interpreter session  \n66: **WHEN** invoking code and file operations  \n67: **THEN** the system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Command Non-Zero Exit\n70: \n71: **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`  \n72: **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed  \n73: **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Python Code Execution Path\n76: \n77: **GIVEN** `language` parameter is `python`, `py`, or `python3`  \n78: **WHEN** `run_code` executes  \n79: **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`.\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Lifecycle Management\n84: \n85: **GIVEN** the need to invoke Agent Runtime workloads  \n86: **WHEN** constructing and using `AgentRuntimeClient`  \n87: **THEN** the system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Context Manager\n90: \n91: **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager  \n92: **WHEN** the block exits  \n93: **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`.\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Bootstrap Session ID\n96: \n97: **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided to `AgentRuntimeClient`  \n98: **WHEN** the client initializes  \n99: **THEN** it SHALL perform a `GET` request to `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read the header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if the header is missing, it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`.\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Invoke Without Session\n102: \n103: **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy  \n104: **WHEN** `invoke` is called on `AgentRuntimeClient`  \n105: **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`.\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: HTTP Client Contracts — Control Plane\n110: \n111: **GIVEN** the need to communicate with the Workload Manager  \n112: **WHEN** making control plane calls  \n113: **THEN** the system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Create Session\n116: \n117: **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` is called  \n118: **WHEN** the request succeeds  \n119: **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if the field is absent.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Delete Session\n122: \n123: **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)` is called  \n124: **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 404  \n125: **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`.\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and Auth\n128: \n129: **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted  \n130: **WHEN** the client initializes  \n131: **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` argument or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present SHALL set header `Authorization: Bearer {token}`.\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: HTTP Client Contracts — Data Plane (Code Interpreter)\n136: \n137: **GIVEN** the need to execute code via the Router  \n138: **WHEN** making data plane calls  \n139: **THEN** the system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Execute Command\n142: \n143: **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called  \n144: **WHEN** the client posts to `api/execute`  \n145: **THEN** the request body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124).\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Write File\n148: \n149: **GIVEN** `write_file` is called  \n150: **WHEN** the client posts to the files API  \n151: **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64-encoded `content`, `path`, and `mode` `\"0644\"`.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Upload File\n154: \n155: **GIVEN** `upload_file` is called  \n156: **WHEN** the client posts to the files API  \n157: **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ### Requirement: HTTP Client Contracts — Data Plane (Agent Runtime)\n162: \n163: **GIVEN** the need to invoke Agent Runtime via the Router  \n164: **WHEN** making data plane calls  \n165: **THEN** the system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Invoke Timeout Tuple\n168: \n169: **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called  \n170: **WHEN** the request is sent  \n171: **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`.\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ### Requirement: Session Header Management\n176: \n177: **GIVEN** the need to identify sessions across Router requests  \n178: **WHEN** constructing HTTP requests  \n179: **THEN** the system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter Session Header\n182: \n183: **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed  \n184: **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs  \n185: **THEN** the session SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST).\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: Exception Hierarchy\n190: \n191: **GIVEN** the need for structured error handling  \n192: **WHEN** errors occur  \n193: **THEN** the system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Command Failure\n196: \n197: **GIVEN** a remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON  \n198: **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response  \n199: **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`).\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: SessionError/DataPlaneError Availability\n202: \n203: **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`  \n204: **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`  \n205: **THEN** these classes SHALL be defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`).\n206: \n207: ---\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Timeout Behavior\n210: \n211: **GIVEN** the need for configurable timeouts  \n212: **WHEN** making HTTP requests  \n213: **THEN** the system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Per-Call Override for Code Execution\n216: \n217: **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)` is called  \n218: **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`  \n219: **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic.\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient Constructor Timeouts\n222: \n223: **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)` is constructed  \n224: **WHEN** `invoke` is called without explicit `timeout` parameter  \n225: **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default).\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ## Public Package Surface\n230: \n231: **GIVEN** the package is imported  \n232: **WHEN** accessing `agentcube/__init__.py`  \n233: **THEN** it SHALL export only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n234: \n235: **GIVEN** `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` is imported  \n236: **WHEN** accessing its exports  \n237: **THEN** it SHALL export `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `__all__` (not in root `__all__`).\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ## Configuration Resolution\n242: \n243: **GIVEN** no dedicated configuration dataclass exists  \n244: **WHEN** resolving settings  \n245: **THEN** defaults and environment resolution SHALL be distributed across components:\n246: \n247: | Component | Resolved settings |\n248: |-----------|-------------------|\n249: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n250: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n251: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n252: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n253: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## Dependencies\n258: \n259: **GIVEN** the package is installed  \n260: **WHEN** resolving dependencies  \n261: **THEN** it SHALL require:\n262: - `requests`\n263: - `PyJWT>=2.0.0`\n264: - `cryptography`\n265: - Python `>=3.10`\n266: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ## API Reference\n271: \n272: ### CodeInterpreterClient\n273: \n274: ```python\n275: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n276:     def __init__(\n277:         self,\n278:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n279:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n280:         ttl: int = 3600,\n281:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n282:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n283:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n284:         verbose: bool = False,\n285:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n286:     ): ...\n287: \n288:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n289:     def __enter__(self): ...\n290:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n291:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n292:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n293:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n294:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n295:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n296:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n297:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n301: \n302: ```python\n303: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n304:     def __init__(\n305:         self,\n306:         agent_name: str,\n307:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n308:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n309:         verbose: bool = False,\n310:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n311:         timeout: int = 120,\n312:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n313:     ): ...\n314: \n315:     def __enter__(self): ...\n316:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n317:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n318:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n319: ```\n320: \n321: ### ControlPlaneClient\n322: \n323: ```python\n324: class ControlPlaneClient:\n325:     def __init__(\n326:         self,\n327:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n328:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n329:         timeout: int = 120,\n330:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n331:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n332:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n333:     ): ...\n334: \n335:     def create_session(\n336:         self,\n337:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n338:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n339:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n340:         ttl: int = 3600,\n341:     ) -> str: ...\n342: \n343:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n344:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n345: ```\n346: \n347: ### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n348: \n349: ```python\n350: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n351:     def __init__(\n352:         self,\n353:         session_id: str,\n354:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n355:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n356:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n357:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n358:         timeout: int = 120,\n359:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n360:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n361:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n362:     ): ...\n363: \n364:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n365:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n366:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n367:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n368:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n369:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n370:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n371:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n375: \n376: ```python\n377: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n378:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n379: \n380:     def __init__(\n381:         self,\n382:         router_url: str,\n383:         namespace: str,\n384:         agent_name: str,\n385:         timeout: int = 120,\n386:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n387:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n388:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n389:     ): ...\n390: \n391:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n392:     def invoke(\n393:         self,\n394:         session_id: str,\n395:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n396:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n397:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n398: \n399:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n400: ```\n401: \n402: ### Utility Functions\n403: \n404: ```python\n405: def create_session(\n406:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n407:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n408: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n409: \n410: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n411: \n412: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n413: ```\n414: \n415: ---\n416: \n417: ## Exception Hierarchy\n418: \n419: ```python\n420: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n421:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n422:     pass\n423: \n424: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n425:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n426:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n427:         self.stderr = stderr\n428:         self.command = command\n429:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n430: \n431: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n432:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n433:     pass\n434: \n435: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n436:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n437:     pass\n438: ```\n439: \n440: ---\n441: \n442: ## HTTP Contract Reference\n443: \n444: ### Control Plane — HTTP\n445: \n446: | Method | Path | Notes |\n447: |--------|------|-------|\n448: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n449: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n450: \n451: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n452: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n453: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n454: \n455: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n456: \n457: ### Data Plane (Code Interpreter) — HTTP\n458: \n459: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n460: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n461: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n462: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n463: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n464: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n465: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n466: \n467: **Headers:**\n468: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n469: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n470: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n471: \n472: **Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n473: \n474: ### Data Plane (Agent Runtime) — HTTP\n475: \n476: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n477: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n478: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n479: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n480: \n481: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n482: \n483: ---\n484: \n485: ## File Index\n486: \n487: | Path | Purpose |\n488: |------|---------|\n489: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n490: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation |\n491: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation |\n492: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n493: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Client re-exports |\n494: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` implementation |\n495: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n496: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n497: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` utility |\n498: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` utility |\n499: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` utility |\n500: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Utils package marker |\n501: | `pyproject.toml` | Package configuration |\n\n(End of file - total 501 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-027  \n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Target:** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`, `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `agentcube/clients/`\n\nThis delta specification defines the behavior and acceptance criteria for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`), which provides Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\n---\n\n## Package Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775905224432,"end":1775905224450}}}}
