{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905408832,"sessionID":"ses_283ce9db5ffevQxE8Wzt5NGV5h","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3362010019L3GqrqJB6DQvT","messageID":"msg_d7c33373b001uWtUpEbJFwzjJG","sessionID":"ses_283ce9db5ffevQxE8Wzt5NGV5h","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-028  \n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Target:** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n\nThis delta specification defines the acceptance criteria for the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`), which provides a Python client for invoking Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane).\n\n---\n\n## Package Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports (add `AgentRuntimeClient` to `__all__`) |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports (add `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` to `__all__`) |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement 1: AgentRuntimeClient Constructor and Configuration\n\n**GIVEN** the need to configure an Agent Runtime client  \n**WHEN** constructing `AgentRuntimeClient`  \n**THEN** the system SHALL support agent identification, connection settings, and optional session management.\n\n#### Scenario 1.1: Router URL from Argument\n\n**GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router:8080\"` is provided as constructor argument  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")` is instantiated  \n**THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080\"`\n\n#### Scenario 1.2: Router URL from Environment Variable\n\n**GIVEN** `router_url` argument is `None` and environment variable `ROUTER_URL=\"http://env-router:9090\"` is set  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated  \n**THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be `\"http://env-router:9090\"`\n\n#### Scenario 1.3: Router URL Missing Raises ValueError\n\n**GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated  \n**THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message explaining Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario 1.4: Default Namespace Assignment\n\n**GIVEN** `namespace` argument is not provided  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated  \n**THEN** `self.namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n\n#### Scenario 1.5: Custom Namespace Assignment\n\n**GIVEN** `namespace=\"production\"` is provided  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", namespace=\"production\")` is instantiated  \n**THEN** `self.namespace` SHALL be `\"production\"`\n\n#### Scenario 1.6: Timeout Configuration Defaults\n\n**GIVEN** no timeout arguments are provided  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated  \n**THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n\n#### Scenario 1.7: Custom Timeout Configuration\n\n**GIVEN** `timeout=300` and `connect_timeout=10.0` are provided  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0)` is instantiated  \n**THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `300` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `10.0`\n\n#### Scenario 1.8: Logger Initialization\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is being instantiated with any valid configuration  \n**WHEN** the constructor runs  \n**THEN** `self.logger` SHALL be initialized via `get_logger(f\"{__name__}.AgentRuntimeClient\")`\n\n#### Scenario 1.9: Verbose Logging Mode\n\n**GIVEN** `verbose=True` is provided  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", verbose=True)` is instantiated  \n**THEN** the logger level SHALL be set to `DEBUG`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement 2: Session ID Bootstrap\n\n**GIVEN** the need to establish a session with the Agent Runtime  \n**WHEN** initializing the client without a provided session_id  \n**THEN** the system SHALL bootstrap a new `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` request.\n\n#### Scenario 2.1: Bootstrap Session ID from GET Request\n\n**GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided during construction  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated  \n**THEN** it SHALL send a `GET` request to `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario 2.2: Session ID Extracted from Response Header\n\n**GIVEN** the bootstrap `GET` request returns a response with header `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123-xyz`  \n**WHEN** the response is received  \n**THEN** `self.session_id` SHALL be `\"abc-123-xyz\"`\n\n#### Scenario 2.3: Missing Session Header Raises ValueError\n\n**GIVEN** the bootstrap `GET` request returns a response without the `x-agentcube-session-id` header  \n**WHEN** the response is processed  \n**THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario 2.4: Provided Session ID Reused\n\n**GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-456\"` is provided during construction  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", session_id=\"existing-session-456\")` is instantiated  \n**THEN** no bootstrap `GET` request SHALL be made and `self.session_id` SHALL be `\"existing-session-456\"`\n\n#### Scenario 2.5: Data Plane Client Initialization\n\n**GIVEN** session bootstrap succeeds or session_id is provided  \n**WHEN** initialization completes  \n**THEN** `self.dp_client` SHALL be an instance of `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` configured with the resolved `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, and timeout settings\n\n---\n\n### Requirement 3: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** the need to communicate with the Agent Runtime data plane  \n**WHEN** making HTTP requests  \n**THEN** the system SHALL provide an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class that handles HTTP communication with proper URL construction and session management.\n\n#### Scenario 3.1: Base URL Construction\n\n**GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router:8080\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`  \n**WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated  \n**THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\"`\n\n#### Scenario 3.2: Session Header Constant Defined\n\n**GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class is defined  \n**WHEN** accessing the class attribute  \n**THEN** `SESSION_HEADER` SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario 3.3: HTTP Session Creation with Pooling\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is being instantiated with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`  \n**WHEN** the constructor runs  \n**THEN** it SHALL call `create_session(pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` to initialize `self.session`\n\n#### Scenario 3.4: Bootstrap Session ID Method\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance exists with valid configuration  \n**WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called  \n**THEN** it SHALL send a `GET` request to `self.base_url` and return the value of the `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n\n---\n\n### Requirement 4: Invoke Operation\n\n**GIVEN** a valid session with the Agent Runtime  \n**WHEN** invoking the Agent Runtime with a payload  \n**THEN** the system SHALL send a `POST` request with JSON payload and session headers.\n\n#### Scenario 4.1: Invoke with Payload Sends POST Request\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid `session_id`  \n**WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"input\": \"hello\", \"params\": {\"temperature\": 0.7}})` is called  \n**THEN** it SHALL send a `POST` request to `self.base_url` with JSON body `{\"input\": \"hello\", \"params\": {\"temperature\": 0.7}}`\n\n#### Scenario 4.2: Invoke Includes Session Header\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` has `session_id=\"sess-123\"`  \n**WHEN** `invoke(payload={})` is called  \n**THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: sess-123`\n\n#### Scenario 4.3: Invoke Includes Content-Type Header\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized  \n**WHEN** `invoke(payload={})` is called  \n**THEN** the request SHALL include header `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n#### Scenario 4.4: Invoke Without Session ID Raises ValueError\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` has `session_id` that is falsy (`None` or empty string)  \n**WHEN** `invoke(payload={})` is called  \n**THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"`\n\n#### Scenario 4.5: Invoke Returns Response Body\n\n**GIVEN** the `POST` request returns a response with body `{\"output\": \"result\", \"status\": \"success\"}`  \n**WHEN** `invoke(payload={})` is called  \n**THEN** it SHALL return the parsed JSON response body\n\n#### Scenario 4.6: Invoke with Custom Timeout\n\n**GIVEN** `invoke(payload={}, timeout=300)` is called  \n**WHEN** the request is sent  \n**THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `300` seconds\n\n#### Scenario 4.7: Invoke Without Timeout Uses Default\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` was initialized with `timeout=120` (default)  \n**WHEN** `invoke(payload={}, timeout=None)` is called  \n**THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 120)` where `connect_timeout` is the instance's `connect_timeout` value\n\n---\n\n### Requirement 5: Context Manager Support\n\n**GIVEN** the need for automatic resource cleanup  \n**WHEN** using `AgentRuntimeClient` as a context manager  \n**THEN** the system SHALL properly manage the lifecycle and close resources on exit.\n\n#### Scenario 5.1: Context Manager Enter Returns Self\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized  \n**WHEN** `with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:` is entered  \n**THEN** `client` SHALL be the `AgentRuntimeClient` instance\n\n#### Scenario 5.2: Context Manager Exit Closes Session on Normal Exit\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager  \n**WHEN** the context block exits normally (without exception)  \n**THEN** `close()` SHALL be called on the underlying `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n#### Scenario 5.3: Context Manager Exit Closes on Exception\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager  \n**WHEN** the context block exits due to an exception  \n**THEN** `close()` SHALL still be called on the underlying `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` before the exception propagates\n\n#### Scenario 5.4: Explicit Close Method\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized and active  \n**WHEN** `close()` is called explicitly  \n**THEN** the underlying data plane client's session SHALL be closed\n\n---\n\n### Requirement 6: Timeout Behavior Consistency\n\n**GIVEN** the need for predictable timeout handling  \n**WHEN** configuring and using timeouts  \n**THEN** the system SHALL maintain consistent default and configurable timeout behavior.\n\n#### Scenario 6.1: Default Timeout Values\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with no timeout overrides  \n**WHEN** accessing timeout attributes  \n**THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n\n#### Scenario 6.2: Timeout Passed to Data Plane Client\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0)` is initialized  \n**WHEN** `self.dp_client` is created  \n**THEN** the data plane client SHALL receive `timeout=300` and `connect_timeout=10.0`\n\n#### Scenario 6.3: Per-Invoke Timeout Override\n\n**GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with default `timeout=120`  \n**WHEN** `invoke(payload={}, timeout=60)` is called  \n**THEN** the request SHALL use `60` as the read timeout, not the default `120`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement 7: Public API Exports\n\n**GIVEN** the need for a clean public API surface  \n**WHEN** importing from the package  \n**THEN** the system SHALL properly export `AgentRuntimeClient` for public use.\n\n#### Scenario 7.1: Root Package Exports AgentRuntimeClient\n\n**GIVEN** the `agentcube/__init__.py` module  \n**WHEN** inspecting `__all__`  \n**THEN** it SHALL contain `\"AgentRuntimeClient\"`\n\n#### Scenario 7.2: Root Import Works\n\n**GIVEN** the package is installed  \n**WHEN** executing `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`  \n**THEN** it SHALL succeed without errors\n\n#### Scenario 7.3: Clients Submodule Re-Exports Data Plane Client\n\n**GIVEN** the `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` module  \n**WHEN** inspecting `__all__`  \n**THEN** it SHALL contain `\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"` for advanced users who need direct access\n\n---\n\n### Requirement 8: Logging and Debugging\n\n**GIVEN** the need for debugging capabilities  \n**WHEN** performing operations  \n**THEN** the system SHALL provide appropriate logging for troubleshooting.\n\n#### Scenario 8.1: Bootstrap Logging\n\n**GIVEN** `verbose=True` or logger level is `DEBUG`  \n**WHEN** session bootstrap is performed  \n**THEN** debug messages SHALL be logged indicating the bootstrap `GET` request and response\n\n#### Scenario 8.2: Invoke Logging\n\n**GIVEN** `verbose=True` or logger level is `DEBUG`  \n**WHEN** `invoke()` is called  \n**THEN** debug messages SHALL be logged with the payload and response status\n\n#### Scenario 8.3: Error Logging\n\n**GIVEN** an error occurs during bootstrap or invoke  \n**WHEN** the error is raised  \n**THEN** error messages SHALL be logged with appropriate context before raising\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Resolution\n\n| Component | Resolved Settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `namespace` ← arg (default: `\"default\"`); `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane; `agent_name` required; `verbose` controls log level; `session_id` optional |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `base_url` constructed from `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Error Condition | Exception Type | Message |\n|----------------|----------------|---------|\n| Router URL missing | `ValueError` | Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable |\n| Session ID header missing on bootstrap | `ValueError` | Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id |\n| Invoke without session | `ValueError` | AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized |\n| HTTP errors | `requests.exceptions.*` | Pass through from requests library |\n\n---\n\n## API Reference\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ): ...\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n**Instance Fields:**\n- `agent_name: str` — Name of the Agent Runtime to invoke\n- `namespace: str` — Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`)\n- `router_url: str` — Router base URL for data plane calls\n- `session_id: Optional[str]` — Session identifier for request routing\n- `timeout: int` — Default read timeout in seconds (default: `120`)\n- `connect_timeout: float` — Connection timeout in seconds (default: `5.0`)\n- `logger: logging.Logger` — Configured logger instance\n- `dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` — Underlying data plane client\n- `verbose: bool` — Whether verbose logging is enabled\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## HTTP Contract Reference\n\n### Data Plane (Agent Runtime)\n\n| Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` | (default session headers) | — |\n| `POST` | `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n**Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n\n---\n\n## Test Coverage Requirements\n\nThe implementation SHALL include unit tests covering:\n\n1. **Constructor Configuration:**\n   - Router URL from argument and environment variable\n   - Router URL missing raises ValueError\n   - Namespace default and custom values\n   - Timeout default and custom values\n   - Verbose mode enables debug logging\n\n2. **Session Bootstrap:**\n   - Successful session ID extraction from header\n   - Missing header raises ValueError\n   - Provided session ID skips bootstrap\n   - Data plane client initialization with correct parameters\n\n3. **Invoke Operation:**\n   - Successful invocation with payload\n   - Session header included in request\n   - Content-Type header set correctly\n   - Invoke without session raises ValueError\n   - Response body returned and parsed\n   - Custom timeout override\n   - Default timeout when not specified\n\n4. **Context Manager:**\n   - Enter returns client instance\n   - Exit closes session on normal completion\n   - Exit closes session on exception\n   - Explicit close method functionality\n\n5. **Timeout Behavior:**\n   - Default values applied\n   - Custom values passed to data plane\n   - Per-invoke override takes precedence\n\n6. **Public API:**\n   - AgentRuntimeClient exported from root\n   - AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient exported from clients submodule\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Add `AgentRuntimeClient` to `__all__` |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Add `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` to `__all__` |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775905408744,"end":1775905408829}}}}
